  "source": "Theorem:\n. \"Theorem 4.11\"\ngiven:\n. X is \\set\nwhere:\n. X is? \\(finite)::set\nthen:\n. have:\n  . forAll: A is \\set\n    where:\n    . A \"in\" X\n    then:\n    . not:\n      . A = \\empty.set\n  iff:\n  . exists: f is \\choice.function:on{X}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"A finite collection $X$ of sets has a choice function if and only if no set in $X$ is empty. The forward direction is Proposition 4.10; the reverse is proved by induction on the cardinality of $X$.\"\nId: \"532996b0-e015-492f-9ea7-c312ebf89aa0\"",
